                  <summary>Inscribed dedication to Zeus.</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">4 lines of text, badly eroded on left side.  Letter height: ca. 4 cm., diminishing to 3 cm at bottom.</note>
                     <note type="general">Dedication to Isis on behalf of Trajan and the imperial familia by Papiris, interpreter and secretary during the prefecture of M. Rutilius Lupus.</note>
                     <note type="general">This block was reused in the same wall of a substantial structure from the late fourth to fifth cent. A.D. as O.Ber. II 118 and 119.</note>
